<cite>M.  S. Boddy (2003) "Imperfect Match:  PDDL 2.1 and Real Applications", Volume 20, pages 133-137</cite>
<p class="media"><a href="/media/1994/live-1994-2432-jair.pdf">PDF</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="/media/1994/live-1994-2431-jair.ps.Z">PostScript</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href='http://dx.doi.org/10.1613/jair.1994'>doi:10.1613/jair.1994</a></p>
<p>PDDL was originally conceived and constructed as a lingua franca for the International Planning Competition.  PDDL2.1 embodies a set of extensions intended to support the expression of something closer to ``real planning problems.''  This objective has only been partially achieved, due in large part to a deliberate focus on not moving too far from classical planning models and solution methods.</p>
